## Operation Reference

| Operation | Script | Use |
|---|---|---|
| Inspect PR | `babysit-pr.sh <repo> <pr-num>` | Refresh facts before judgement |
| Send worker message | `send-to-worker.sh <profile> <session-id> <msg-file>` | Same-PR `/smithy.fix` only |
| Request rebase | `request-rebase.sh <profile> <session-id> <worktree-path>` | Stale-main CI failure |
| Re-trigger CI | `rerun-ci.sh <repo> <run-id>` | Transient CI failure |
| List workers | `list-workers.sh <profile> <worker-group>` | Diagnosis only |

## Standing Rules

- One Smithy step equals one PR. Never chain into new work from this skill.
- `/smithy.fix` reuses the existing worker and PR.
- Merge decisions belong to `legate.merge` or the operator.
- Discovery, routine review-thread fixes, first conflict prompts, and all-clear transitions belong to the deterministic loop.
- If acting would bypass a merge gate or duplicate a loop action, stop and surface `NEED:`.
